<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Flagellar verticils 2 times longer than corresponding segment, but shorter in some specimens. Prescutum with one very broad brown mid-longitudinal stripe. Wings yellow variegated with grayish smoky markings, and three grayish spots at basal Rs, apical Sc and R2; Sc1 apically reaching 1/2-3/4 of Rs. Gonostylus long and slender. Posterior margin of tergite 9 emarginated. Gonostylus with sharp apex and swollen base. Apex of paramere ended at 3/4 of aedeagus. Ventral margin of aedeagus with H-shaped. Female, hypogynial valve 2.3 times longer than wide at base.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="redescription">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Redescription.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Male (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">n</emphasis>
= 13): body length 6-8 mm, wing length 7-8 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Head</emphasis>
dull brown (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 45–47" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figures 45 - 47. Limonia sylvicola, male 45 male habitus, lateral view 46 head and thorax, dorsal view 47 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures45-47" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456146" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">45</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 45–47" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figures 45 - 47. Limonia sylvicola, male 45 male habitus, lateral view 46 head and thorax, dorsal view 47 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures45-47" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456146" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">46</figureCitation>
). Vertex dull brown, with two yellow markings at outer margin near eyes (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 45–47" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figures 45 - 47. Limonia sylvicola, male 45 male habitus, lateral view 46 head and thorax, dorsal view 47 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures45-47" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456146" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">46</figureCitation>
). Occiput dull yellow, covered with black setulae. Antenna yellow and 14-segmented; scape and pedicel dull brown; flagellomeres nearly cylindrical; flagellar verticils grayish yellow, 2 times longer than corresponding segment but short in some specimens. Nasus 1/2 as long as rostrum. Rostrum brown or dull brown. Labella pale yellow, except inner margin brown. Palpi brown, with black setulae.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures45-47" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456146" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" start="Figures 45–47" startId="F15">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Figures 45-47.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schummel" baseAuthorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Limoniidae" genus="Limonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Limonia sylvicola" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sylvicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Limonia sylvicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">45</emphasis>
male habitus, lateral view 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">46</emphasis>
head and thorax, dorsal view 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">47</emphasis>
right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Thorax</emphasis>
mostly brownish yellow (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 45–47" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figures 45 - 47. Limonia sylvicola, male 45 male habitus, lateral view 46 head and thorax, dorsal view 47 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures45-47" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456146" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">45</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 45–47" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figures 45 - 47. Limonia sylvicola, male 45 male habitus, lateral view 46 head and thorax, dorsal view 47 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures45-47" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456146" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">46</figureCitation>
). Cervical sclerite pale brown, with black outer margin. Pronotum dark brown, with black setulae. Prescutum with broad, brown longitudinal stripe, and with black setulae at lateral margin. Scutum brown, with black setulae at outer margin. Scutellum pale yellow, but mid-anterior margin with round, yellow marking. Mediotergite dull brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 45–47" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figures 45 - 47. Limonia sylvicola, male 45 male habitus, lateral view 46 head and thorax, dorsal view 47 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures45-47" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456146" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">46</figureCitation>
). Mesopleura dull yellow; subspiracular sclerite brownish yellow; anepimeron and katepisternum with black setulae. Legs with coxae and trochanters yellow, except frontal coxae brown; femora yellow, with one dark-brown subapical ring; tibiae yellow, with reddish-brown subapical ring; tarsi yellow to dark brown onwards. Setulae on legs black. Wings yellow, variegated with grayish smoky markings, and three grayish spots at basal Rs, apical Sc, and R2; Sc1 apically reaching 1/2-3/4 of Rs; basal deflection of CuA1 beyond branching point of M; some specimens R2 absent in some specimens (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 45–47" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figures 45 - 47. Limonia sylvicola, male 45 male habitus, lateral view 46 head and thorax, dorsal view 47 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures45-47" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456146" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">47</figureCitation>
). Halter: stem white; knob dull gray.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Abdomen</emphasis>
mainly brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 45–47" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figures 45 - 47. Limonia sylvicola, male 45 male habitus, lateral view 46 head and thorax, dorsal view 47 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures45-47" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456146" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">45</figureCitation>
). Sternite 8 reddish brown. Each abdominal segment with one pale-brown ring at posterior margin. Abdomen covered with golden setulae. Abdominal segments 7-8 reddish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Hypopygium</emphasis>
reddish brown (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 48–52" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figures 48 - 52. Limonia sylvicola, male 48 hypopygium, dorsal view 49 hypopygium, ventral view 50 hypopygium, lateral view 51 aedeagus and paramere 52 habitat, Hemu, Burqin, Xinjiang, China on 22 June 2017. Scale bars: = 0.1 mm (48 - 51)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures48-52" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456147" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">49-51</figureCitation>
). Posterior margin of tergite 9 emarginated (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 48–52" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figures 48 - 52. Limonia sylvicola, male 48 hypopygium, dorsal view 49 hypopygium, ventral view 50 hypopygium, lateral view 51 aedeagus and paramere 52 habitat, Hemu, Burqin, Xinjiang, China on 22 June 2017. Scale bars: = 0.1 mm (48 - 51)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures48-52" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456147" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">48</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxite long cylindrical. Gonostylus with sharp apex and swollen base covered with black setulae (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 48–52" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figures 48 - 52. Limonia sylvicola, male 48 hypopygium, dorsal view 49 hypopygium, ventral view 50 hypopygium, lateral view 51 aedeagus and paramere 52 habitat, Hemu, Burqin, Xinjiang, China on 22 June 2017. Scale bars: = 0.1 mm (48 - 51)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures48-52" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456147" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">48</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 48–52" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figures 48 - 52. Limonia sylvicola, male 48 hypopygium, dorsal view 49 hypopygium, ventral view 50 hypopygium, lateral view 51 aedeagus and paramere 52 habitat, Hemu, Burqin, Xinjiang, China on 22 June 2017. Scale bars: = 0.1 mm (48 - 51)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures48-52" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456147" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">49</figureCitation>
). Paramere with fan-shaped base and sharp apex, ending at 3/4 of aedeagus (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 48–52" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figures 48 - 52. Limonia sylvicola, male 48 hypopygium, dorsal view 49 hypopygium, ventral view 50 hypopygium, lateral view 51 aedeagus and paramere 52 habitat, Hemu, Burqin, Xinjiang, China on 22 June 2017. Scale bars: = 0.1 mm (48 - 51)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures48-52" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456147" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">49-51</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus forked; ventral margin with mid-protrusion triangular in lateral view; ventral margin with uniquely H-shaped pattern in middle and anterior margin fish-tail-like in shape (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 48–52" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figures 48 - 52. Limonia sylvicola, male 48 hypopygium, dorsal view 49 hypopygium, ventral view 50 hypopygium, lateral view 51 aedeagus and paramere 52 habitat, Hemu, Burqin, Xinjiang, China on 22 June 2017. Scale bars: = 0.1 mm (48 - 51)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures48-52" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456147" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">49</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 48–52" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figures 48 - 52. Limonia sylvicola, male 48 hypopygium, dorsal view 49 hypopygium, ventral view 50 hypopygium, lateral view 51 aedeagus and paramere 52 habitat, Hemu, Burqin, Xinjiang, China on 22 June 2017. Scale bars: = 0.1 mm (48 - 51)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures48-52" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456147" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">51</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
